{"word":"H3334 - יָצַר - yâtsar - yaw-tsar' - Be distressed","slug":"H3334","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יָצַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yâtsar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yaw-tsar'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Be distressed"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E6;&#x05E8; - ya&#x0302;tsar</b> - <i>yaw-tsar'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>press</i> (intransitively), that is, <i>be narrow</i>; figuratively <i>be in distress: - </i>be distressed, be narrow, be straitened (in straits), be vexed."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1222\">H1222</a>, <a href=\"#/H4712\">H4712</a>, <a href=\"#/H6862\">H6862</a>, <a href=\"#/H6869\">H6869</a>, <a href=\"#/H6872\">H6872</a>, <a href=\"#/H6887\">H6887</a>"}]}